[section 1 Making Checks]

To make a check, roll 1d20 and add the relevant attribute bonus. If the result
is greater than or equal to the target value, you succeed.

Checks can be made with Size and Evd, even though they are not core attributes.

Often, the game will ask you to make checks against other creatures. Such a
check is notated [qmark the attribute of the creature making the check vs
the other creature's attribute]. You make a check
with your attribute, where the target number is 10 + the other creature's attribute.

