When you become a druid, choose one of the following options:

[text ib Animal Companion.] You have an animal companion, which can be of any
type approved by the GM. It has +2 Int, +1 Per, and +1 health. You can
communicate verbally with this companion.

[text ib Beast Shape.] A number of times per day equal to your Per bonus, you
can assume the form of any size 2 or smaller animal. You take on that creature's
Str, Dex, and Spd scores, as well as its evasion, health, armor, and any
other special abilities (such as the ability to swim, fly, or breathe
underwater). If you are reduced to zero health while in animal form, you return
to your regular form with the amount of health you had when you transformed
minus two.

[section 2 Fighters]

You are proficient with weapons up to d10 and armor up to type 6.

When you become a fighter, choose up to two hand's worth of weapons or shields
to be your signature armament. While wielding your signature armament, you get
bonuses based on the type of equipment you're wielding.
